						In August 2017, the people of Rohingya confronted brutal
						genocide in Myanmar, leaving them displaced and
						devastated. Hundreds and thousands were reported dead,
						while many began to flee to Bangladesh in a traumatic
						state.
					</p>
					<p class="text-white mt-4 sm:text-xs md:text-lg text-left">
						As of now, after the Rohingya crisis, there are
						approximately over 1 million refugees who are managing
						their survival in the highly populated Cox’s Bazar,
						recorded as the largest refugee camp in the world. To
						alleviate their suffering, Al-Wahab Foundation is on the
						ground to provide sustenance for better survival through
						the Rohingya Emergency Appeal.
					</p>
